<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Koeberlinia</i> <i>spinosa</i> is dominant or characteristically present in the shrub canopy with species including <i>Ambrosia</i> <i>dumosa</i> and <i>Larrea</i> <i>tridentata</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 5 m; canopy is intermittent to continuous. Herbaceous layer is sparse with seasonal annuals. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Washes and rocky slopes with desert pavement. Soils are coarse sands. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Koeberlinia spinosa</i> ssp. <i>tenuispina</i> as an UPL plants. </div>
</div>

        
