    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        
            <p><i>Koeberlinia spinosa</i> occurs in the Chocolate Mountains and in the Picacho Peak area in the Sonoran Desert (322Be). <i>K. spinosa</i> appears to grow among the drier associations of the <i>Larrea tridentata- Ambrosia dumosa</i> alliance as small dense thickets of one or a few individuals. We need further information to understand the relationship of this species in stateâ€™s desert vegetation.</p>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Sonoran Desert</b> (322Bc, Be). None</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
